\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Distribution of annotated bounding boxes per image in the BBBC041 training set (1,208 images). The dashed red line marks the median (59 boxes); the dotted orange line at 100 boxes identifies images we classify as \emph  {dense smears}. 11\% of images exceed this threshold. 58\% of a 200-image sample contain at least one overlapping cell pair ($\text  {IoU}>0.3$), confirming the severity of the NMS failure mode.}}{4}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:density}{{4}{4}{Distribution of annotated bounding boxes per image in the BBBC041 training set (1,208 images). The dashed red line marks the median (59 boxes); the dotted orange line at 100 boxes identifies images we classify as \emph {dense smears}. 11\% of images exceed this threshold. 58\% of a 200-image sample contain at least one overlapping cell pair ($\text {IoU}>0.3$), confirming the severity of the NMS failure mode}{figure.4}{}}
