\newlabel{fig:architecture}{{1}{5}{\malariai {} two-stage decoupled architecture. Stage~1 performs universal cell segmentation via distance-transform guided watershed on the raw 1600$\times $1200 blood smear image with no annotation input. Stage~2 classifies each 64$\times $64 crop with EfficientNet-B0 and Focal Loss, followed by Grad-CAM\texttt {++} for per-cell spatial explainability}{figure.1}{}}
